title: Rocket to launch China’s next space station module arrives at launch center
summary: A Long March 5B rocket has arrived at Wenchang spaceport as China gears up to send its second space station module into orbit.

title: China prepares for July 24 launch of second space station module
summary: China is gearing up to send a second module to its under-construction space station with a launch from the coastal Wenchang spaceport later this month.

title: China’s heavy-lift Long March 5B rocket rolls out with new space station module
summary: China moved a heavy-lift Long March 5B rocket to its launch pad Monday in preparation for liftoff this weekend with a 22-ton module for the country’s Tiangong space station, a mission that could end with another uncontrolled re-entry of the Long March 5B’s large core stage.
